statement:
Let \(n\) and \(k\) be relatively prime natural numbers with \(k < n\). Each number in the set \(M = \{1, 2, \dots, n - 1\}\) is colored either blue or white. It is given that:
\begin{enumerate}
\item[(i)] for each \(i \in M\), both \(i\) and \(n - i\) have the same color;
\item[(ii)] for each \(i \in M\), \(i \neq k\), both \(i\) and \(|i - k|\) have the same color.
\end{enumerate}
Prove that all numbers in \(M\) must have the same color.
